To promote the new album ahead of its release, Reilly went on tour in the UK supporting Justin Currie and The Proclaimers throughout May and June 2010.
Following this Reilly announced that he would tour again, this time as the headline act throughout September 2010.
On 23 April 2012, Reilly started a PledgeMusic project with the aim to raise funds to enable him to record and independently release his third studio album.
On 26 July 2012 the project had reached 100% of its target.
The album was released to pledgers on 24 July titled Waking A Sleepwalker.
After the intensity of writing and touring his first 3 LPs, Tommy took a year off to complete a Masters at the Glasgow School of Art.
With a fresh perspective he returned working on his 6-track EP ‘Weightless’, released on Gizmo Tunes Recordings in December 2015.

Reilly was shortlisted in the BAFTA Scotland New Talent Awards 2016 (for his work in The Beholder).[1]
The Animaniacs song 'Suffragette Song' won a Daytime Emmy Award for Outstanding Original Song for a Preschool, Children’s or Animated Program, along with Roddy Hart, Andrew Barbot and Jess Lacher.
